<td style="font-size=20;"><b>JMXStopEngine</b></td>
</tr>
<tr valign="top">
<td>Stop a BW Engine using JMX on the given host name and port number.<br>
<br>Requirements:<br>------------------<br>-Need to use BW 5.6 or later version, which supports JMX.<br>
<br>-The following JMX properties need to be set in the bwengine.tra file to enable JMX:<br>java.property.com.sun.management.jmxremote=true<br>java.property.com.sun.management.jmxremote.port=1111<br>java.property.com.sun.management.jmxremote.authenticate=false<br>java.property.com.sun.management.jmxremote.ssl=false<br>Jmx.Enabled=true<br>
<br>-The last property: Jmx.Enabled=true can actually be put into a config file and referred to accordingly<br>
<br>For example, one can start bwengine:<br>
<br>C:\tibco\bw\5.6\bin&gt;bwengine -p bwengine.tra C:\tsi-tests\tests\bw\func\engine\bpel\1.1\1_1<br> 
<br>-The machine host name and port number (e.g. 1111 above) are accessed in order to use JMX to stop the BW engine<br>
</td>
</tr>
